[{"model": "website_app.post", "pk": 1, "fields": {"title": "Uses | The Tools I Use", "content": "<p class=\"\" data-start=\"146\" data-end=\"539\">Over time, I've built up a set of tools that have become key to my development process. These applications help me stay organized (mostly), streamline my workflow, and get things done efficiently.</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"1167\" data-end=\"1205\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Editor</span>: <strong data-start=\"1177\" data-end=\"1205\">VS Code</strong><strong data-start=\"1177\" data-end=\"1205\">&nbsp;/ Neovim</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\"><strong data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1219\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2015\">&loz;&nbsp;</strong>VS Code</strong>: My go-to for feature-rich development.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" style=\"padding-left: 40px;\" data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2061\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2015\"><strong data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1219\">&loz; </strong>N</strong><strong data-start=\"1351\" data-end=\"1370\">eovim</strong>: When I want experiments/efficiency, neovim takes the spotlight. It's insanely fast once you get the hang of it... or so they said.</p>\r\n<blockquote data-start=\"1524\" data-end=\"1623\">\r\n<p><strong data-start=\"1526\" data-end=\"1535\">&gt;Tip</strong>: Neovim is lightweight and <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">highly</span> customizable, offering efficient navigation, seamless editing, and extensive plugin integration with the OS, window management, Git, and more.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<div class=\"contain-inline-size rounded-md border-[0.5px] border-token-border-medium relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary\">\r\n<div class=\"flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary dark:bg-token-main-surface-secondary select-none rounded-t-[5px]\">\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../../media/media_files/nvim-rdt.png\" alt=\"nvim-rdt\" width=\"1039\" height=\"649\"></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><em>**Neovim example config set from <a title=\"neovim\" href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/vimporn/comments/1j9anxf/my_first_ever_nvim_setup/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Reddit</a>.&nbsp;</em></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"1167\" data-end=\"1205\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Notes</span>: <strong data-start=\"1177\" data-end=\"1205\">Joplin / Apple Reminders</strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"\" style=\"padding-left: 40px;\" data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1345\"><strong data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1219\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2015\">&loz; </strong>Joplin</strong>: Open-source, Markdown-friendly, and encrypted. A fantastic option for keeping track of ideas and/or development notes.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" style=\"padding-left: 40px;\" data-start=\"1351\" data-end=\"1522\"><strong data-start=\"1351\" data-end=\"1370\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2015\"><strong data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1219\">&loz; </strong></strong>Apple Reminders</strong>: Great for quick tasks beyond just development. It keeps me on top of all things (the phone widget only).</p>\r\n<blockquote data-start=\"1524\" data-end=\"1623\">\r\n<p><strong data-start=\"1526\" data-end=\"1535\">&gt;Side note</strong>: You can sync Joplin across devices for seamless note-taking using a self-hosted service like <strong>Nextcloud</strong>, the official paid&nbsp;<strong data-start=\"133\" data-end=\"149\">Joplin Cloud</strong>, or even <strong>Dropbox</strong> for easy setup. Plus it's multiplatform and you can use it&nbsp;<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">offline</span>.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"1716\" data-end=\"1737\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Browser</span>: <strong data-start=\"1728\" data-end=\"1737\">Brave</strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1176\" data-end=\"1401\">Brave is my browser of choice, blocking ads and trackers while offering a smooth, private experience.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1176\" data-end=\"1401\">That&rsquo;s a win &mdash; especially when paired with <strong><a href=\"https://github.com/pi-hole\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Pi-hole for Raspberry. </a></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" style=\"padding-left: 40px;\" data-start=\"1951\" data-end=\"2003\"><strong data-start=\"1951\" data-end=\"1968\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2015\"><strong data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1219\">&loz; </strong></strong>Privacy-first</strong>: It blocks unwanted ads and trackers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" style=\"padding-left: 40px;\" data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2061\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2015\"><strong data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1219\">&loz; </strong>Speed</strong>: Faster browsing due to less content to load.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" style=\"padding-left: 40px;\" data-start=\"2064\" data-end=\"2112\"><strong data-start=\"2064\" data-end=\"2080\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2015\"><strong data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1219\">&loz; </strong></strong>Extensions</strong>: Supports chromium-based installations.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"2223\" data-end=\"2245\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-decoration: underline;\">Font</span></span>:&nbsp;<strong data-start=\"2232\" data-end=\"2245\">Monaspace</strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2247\" data-end=\"2423\">I've found <strong><a title=\"monaspace\" href=\"https://monaspace.githubnext.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Monaspace</a></strong> to be incredibly clear and easy on the eyes &mdash; perfect for long coding sessions. And it's open source.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2247\" data-end=\"2423\"><img src=\"../../../../../media/media_files/Dracula_monaspaced.png\" alt=\"dracula_monaspace\" width=\"803\" height=\"441\"></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><em>**VS Code Dracula theme with Monaspace Neon font.</em></span></p>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"2580\" data-end=\"2614\">&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"2580\" data-end=\"2614\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Password Manager</span>: <strong data-start=\"2601\" data-end=\"2614\">Bitwarden</strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"\" style=\"padding-left: 40px;\" data-start=\"2793\" data-end=\"2838\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2015\"><strong data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1219\">&loz; </strong></strong>End-to-End Encryption</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" style=\"padding-left: 40px;\" data-start=\"2841\" data-end=\"2892\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2015\"><strong data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1219\">&loz; </strong></strong>Cross-Platform</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" style=\"padding-left: 40px;\" data-start=\"2895\" data-end=\"2937\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2015\"><strong data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1219\">&loz; </strong></strong>Open-Source</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2015\"><strong data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1219\">&loz; </strong></strong>Mobile and 2FA authentication options</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"2580\" data-end=\"2614\">&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"3025\" data-end=\"3059\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">OS &amp; Shell</span>: <strong data-start=\"3042\" data-end=\"3059\">Ubuntu / Fish&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"3025\" data-end=\"3059\"><strong data-start=\"3042\" data-end=\"3059\">&nbsp;<img src=\"../../../../../media/media_files/ubuntu.png\" alt=\"ubuntu\" width=\"168\" height=\"166\"> <img src=\"../../../../../media/media_files/fish.png\" alt=\"fish\" width=\"201\" height=\"159\"></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"3063\" data-end=\"3162\">Ubuntu powers on my PC by default. Recently, I switched to Fish shell &mdash; its smart completions and suggestions make terminal work a breeze.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" style=\"padding-left: 40px;\" data-start=\"3290\" data-end=\"3342\"><strong data-start=\"3290\" data-end=\"3308\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2015\"><strong data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1219\">&loz; </strong></strong>Autocompletion</strong>: Intuitive and smart suggestions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" style=\"padding-left: 40px;\" data-start=\"3345\" data-end=\"3407\"><strong data-start=\"3345\" data-end=\"3368\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2015\"><strong data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1219\">&loz; </strong></strong>Syntax highlighting</strong>: Makes reading command output clearer.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"3543\" data-end=\"3580\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Looking Ahead</span>: <strong>RSS</strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2064\" data-end=\"2175\">... coming soon.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2064\" data-end=\"2175\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"3860\" data-end=\"3886\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Bonus</span>: <strong>A Keyboard Story</strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2217\" data-end=\"2585\">On a slightly different note, I have a bit of a fondness for keyboards. Years ago, while working as an Electrical Officer on a vessel, I stumbled upon an old IBM-like, vintage keyboard in the ship's<s> steering gear</s> garbage room. It was a mechanical marvel with Cherry [ML4100] first switches &mdash; a real piece of history. I used that keyboard for a year; it had a unique feel.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2217\" data-end=\"2585\">&nbsp; <img src=\"../../../../../media/media_files/cherry.jpg\" alt=\"cherry\" width=\"334\" height=\"158\">&nbsp; &nbsp;<img src=\"../../../../../media/media_files/f75.jpg\" alt=\"f75\" width=\"350\" height=\"155\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2587\" data-end=\"2945\">Fast forward to today, and I recently got my hands on a new keyboard: the <strong>EPOMAKER x AULA F-75</strong>. It features&nbsp;<strong><em>LEOBOG <strong>IceVein</strong> </em></strong>linear switches that are incredibly smooth and have a fantastic creamy sound. I even have a recorded sample of a short typing sound clip for you.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2587\" data-end=\"2945\"><audio src=\"../../../../../media/media_files/ASMR_F-75.mp3\" controls=\"controls\"></audio></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2952\" data-end=\"3167\">So, that&rsquo;s it. I hope you found something interesting or inspiring here. See you next time!</p>", "excerpt": "", "date_added": "2025-03-06", "slug": "uses-the-tools-i-use", "owner": 1}}, {"model": "website_app.post", "pk": 5, "fields": {"title": "Crafting the ESP32 Dashboard", "content": "<p>Coming soon...</p>", "excerpt": "", "date_added": "2025-04-10", "slug": "crafting-the-esp32-dashboard", "owner": 1}}, {"model": "website_app.mediafile", "pk": 4, "fields": {"title": "aula_asmr", "file_type": "audio", "file": "media_files/ASMR_F-75.mp3", "uploaded_at": "2025-03-27T13:17:50.011Z"}}, {"model": "website_app.mediafile", "pk": 5, "fields": {"title": "dracula_monaspace", "file_type": "image", "file": "media_files/Dracula_monaspaced.png", "uploaded_at": "2025-03-27T13:47:09.896Z"}}, {"model": "website_app.mediafile", "pk": 7, "fields": {"title": "ubuntu", "file_type": "image", "file": "media_files/ubuntu.png", "uploaded_at": "2025-03-27T14:15:38.781Z"}}, {"model": "website_app.mediafile", "pk": 8, "fields": {"title": "f75", "file_type": "image", "file": "media_files/f75.jpg", "uploaded_at": "2025-03-27T14:15:50.228Z"}}, {"model": "website_app.mediafile", "pk": 9, "fields": {"title": "cherry", "file_type": "image", "file": "media_files/cherry.jpg", "uploaded_at": "2025-03-27T14:16:02.971Z"}}, {"model": "website_app.mediafile", "pk": 10, "fields": {"title": "nvim-setup", "file_type": "image", "file": "media_files/nvim-setup.png", "uploaded_at": "2025-03-27T14:18:34.203Z"}}, {"model": "website_app.mediafile", "pk": 11, "fields": {"title": "fish", "file_type": "image", "file": "media_files/fish.png", "uploaded_at": "2025-03-27T14:25:16.840Z"}}, {"model": "website_app.mediafile", "pk": 12, "fields": {"title": "nvim-dn", "file_type": "image", "file": "media_files/nvim-dn.png", "uploaded_at": "2025-03-27T14:30:23.454Z"}}, {"model": "website_app.mediafile", "pk": 13, "fields": {"title": "nvim-rdt", "file_type": "image", "file": "media_files/nvim-rdt.png", "uploaded_at": "2025-03-27T15:11:49.719Z"}}]